  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc0\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd- \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka to start debt restructuring talks with China - IMF",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "International Monetary Fund has said that Sri Lanka should start debt restructuring talks with China.",
        "Krishna Srinivasan, Director for Asia Pacific of the International Monetary Fund, said that China, the biggest creditor of Sri Lanka, should negotiate positively with China regarding debt restructuring.",
        "The country of 22 million people is facing an economic and political crisis like never before in its history.",
        "Ranil Wickremesinghe, who served six times as Prime Minister, has been sworn in as the President following the removal of the previous President due to a massive popular uprising following months of fuel, food and medicine shortages.",
        "Sri Lanka owes China $6.5 billion in debt, the International Monetary Fund has said.",
        "The world's second largest economy has invested in highways, ports and airports.",
        "Krishna Srinivasan has said that Sri Lanka should enter into debt restructuring negotiations with its private and public creditors.",
        "He mentioned that Sri Lanka should do this to ensure that creditworthiness is re-established.",
        "Sri Lanka has asked the International Monetary Fund to come up with a recovery plan to recover from its worst economic crisis since independence.",
        "Sri Lanka, which has been struggling to make payments to key importers, defaulted on its 12 billion foreign debt and defaulted in April.",
        "The official of the International Monetary Fund has said that we need to see progress on some issues, however, he refused to comment on the major reforms that Sri Lanka needs to carry out in order to achieve compliance with the International Monetary Fund."
      ],
